To scale down the PostgreSQL-HA cluster just perform a normal upgrade setting the *replicaCount* value to the desired number of nodes. For example, reduce the cluster to one replica (primary node) while enabling the *repmgr* extension:

~~~
$ helm upgrade <%= variable :repo_name, :platform %>/postgresql-ha \
--set password=POSTGRESQL_PASSWORD \
--set repmgrPassword=REPMGR_PASSWORD \
--set replicaCount=1 \
--set upgradeRepmgrExtension=true
~~~

> NOTE: You need to substitute the placeholders POSTGRESQL_PASSWORD, and [REPMGR_PASSWORD] with the values obtained from instructions in the installation notes.
